reviews.review: A fitting conclusion to the Star Wars series...
The best movie of the new trilogy, and one of the best in the Star Wars series.
Recommend seeing it in IMAX! WOW well done!!!!! The amount of people in the end credits looked to be hitting the 1,000 marker. LOVED IT!!!!!!!
The pacing was weird.  And SpoilerAlert:  Bringing back the Emperor in the first two lines of the scroll...and making him Rey's grandfather was ridiculous.  Very disappointing movie.
Not really sure why the critics slammed it so bad. I felt it was entertaining and flowed well enough to keep me in it. I felt it had a nice degree of closure to the saga.
Great movie. JJ Abrams payed homage to all the original movies and linked everything together.
I really enjoyed ther movie I grew up with star wars but have not read the books.  This was a great way to end the series from a casual fan.

This movie is off pace, too cheesy, and seems poorly put together. The characters have way to much power and seem more like gods than Jedi. In my opinion, they've destroyed the whole star wars series with this movie, but the acting was good and I'm sure the younger kids who haven't seen all the movies would enjoy this. I literally felt a sick feeling while watching this movie.

I am mixed about this new trilogy.  I liked this movie a hell of a lot better than "the last  jedi", which to me is the worst one in all 9 movies. this trilogy did not get me to like the characters as much as the other 2 trilogies.  Yes the prequels acting SUCKED, but it was the story and the characters I loved, along with the action and special effects.  I really didnt care to much in the Rey/Finn/Poe characters, they jsut didnt grab me like Ahn/Luke/Leia and Anakin/Kenobi/Padme did.  again, yes the acting was poor in the prequels!  there were things loved in the new trilogy but ALOT of bad.  I loved seeing Han/Leia/Luke again (CHEWIE!! and Lando!!) But to me the new triology seemed more like Star Trek scifi!  The Aliens and planets just seemed like Star Trekkie!  No thought behind their creation!  Lucas had an imagination and also the old school props dept!  I was soooo excited to see Force Awakens but sort of disappointed, last jedi was a total let down and this one I really didnt care.  I waited to see if until today!! From ROTJ to TFA I was their the first night, the Last Jedi I saw the next day but was in Japan at the time.   JUst not thrilled about it anymore.  I still watch the original religiously!  The prequels once in awhile but the new ones (TFA and TLJ hardly ever!  I quess I am getting old!! I was 4 yrs old when the first (Episode 4) one came out!! 
But, I did love Rogue One (alittle slow but great) Solo was OK (woody harrleson jsut didnt fit the part to me! he will always be WOODY!).  But I do like the Mandalorian!  IG-## awesome!! :)
Definitely better than I expected, nothing like the originals, but a good ending to the Skywalkers.
